Transfer Learning-Based Classification of Poultry Diseases for Enhanced Health Management

ğŸ¯ Objective
To develop an efficient image classification system using transfer learning that detects poultry diseases based on images of poultry droppings or visible symptoms.
âœ… The goal is to help farmers identify diseases early and manage flock health effectively, even in rural areas.

â— Problem Statement
Poultry diseases like Newcastle Disease, Coccidiosis, and Salmonella cause significant economic losses in the poultry industry.

In rural or resource-limited settings, veterinary support is not always available. A fast, automated image classification system can provide immediate diagnosis, enabling better disease control and reduced mortality.

